{# Extract role + concise focus areas from a job description #}
Extract the most relevant role title and interview focus areas from the job description and return JSON only.

Current role field (may be empty or generic): {{ role }}

Job description:
{{ job_description }}

JSON schema:
{
  "role": string,
  "focus_areas": [string, ...],
  "summary": string
}

Constraints:
- role must be a short role title such as "AI Engineer", "Backend Engineer", "ML Engineer", or similar.
- focus_areas must be short topic labels, not full task descriptions.
- Each focus area should be 2 to 5 words maximum.
- Prefer concise noun phrases such as:
  "RAG pipelines", "Vector databases", "Prompt engineering", "Model evaluation".
- Do NOT start items with verbs like "Design", "Build", "Implement", "Develop", or "Collaborate".
- Return 4 to 6 focus areas only.
- summary must be one short sentence summarizing the main emphasis of the role.